Paper: hep-th/9505121

Date: 1995-05-19

Title: Entanglement Entropy of Nontrivial States

Authors: Eric Benedict and So-Young Pi

Comments: 21 pages, LaTex, 2 figures in separate file

Journal-ref: Annals Phys. 245 (1996) 209-224

We study the entanglement entropy arising from coherent states andone--particle states. We show that it is possible to define a finiteentanglement entropy by subtracting the vacuum entropy from that of theconsidered states, when the unobserved region is the same.